			<div class="entry">
				<p style="text-align: justify;">Welcome to Mobiserv – a European research project on smart technology, started in December 2009 and running until September 2013, by 8 partners from 7 countries, representing care organisations, universities, research institutions and industry.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The objective of the Mobiserv project was to design, develop, and evaluate beyond-state-of-the-art technology to support independent living of older adults as long as possible, in their home or in various degrees of institutionalization, with a focus on health, nutrition, well-being, and safety.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="alignright  wp-image-417" style="border: 1px solid #9c9c9c; margin-left: 20px;" alt="ref_dag_1" src="http://www.mobiserv.info/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/ref_dag_1-300x198.jpg" width="270" height="178" />Support has been delivered in indoor daily living situations, and the implementation has been based on the user-acceptance of the technology and understanding of the user&#8217;s context of use in order to truly addresses user needs.</p>
<h1>The Concept</h1>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Mobiserv has developed a personal intelligent platform consisting of various devices, middleware, and services. The Mobiserv platform consists of the following:</p>
<ul style="text-align: justify;">
<li>A social <strong>companion robot</strong> &#8211; an autonomous robot, containing processing power, data storage capability, various sensors, machine learning/experience gathering/adaptation, a touch screen, speech synthesis, and speech recognition;</li>
<li>Wearable <strong>smart clothes</strong> &#8211; implementing various functionalities such as monitoring of vital signs or sleeping patterns, and detection of falls;</li>
<li>A <strong>smart home</strong> environment &#8211; including smart sensors, optical recognition units, and home automation elements, to detect among others eating and drinking patterns, activity patterns, and dangerous situations.</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-416" alt="Mobiserv_robot_2" src="http://www.mobiserv.info/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Mobiserv_robot_2-133x300.jpg" width="133" height="300" />The prototypes developed are open, both in the sense of being built using open-standards and in their ability to be expanded with new functionalities and components.</p>
<h1>Objectives &amp; Results</h1>
<p style="text-align: justify;">To read, see and experience what the Mobiserv team has achieved, please have a look at the extensive <a title="Results" href="http://www.mobiserv.info/results/">Results section</a>, which includes results per project year, photos and videos.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Visit our <a title="News &amp; Events" href="http://www.mobiserv.info/news-events/">News &amp; Events section</a> to stay up-to-date about the latest Mobiserv news, current activities of the team, the latest results, and upcoming events where Mobiserv will be presented and/or demonstrated.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">To learn about the project&#8217;s detailed and ambitious objectives, have a look at the <a title="Objectives" href="http://www.mobiserv.info/objectives/">Objectives section</a> of this website.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><iframe src="//www.youtube.com/embed/6DFJwnwzhPs?rel=0&amp;cc_lang_pref=en&amp;cc_load_policy=1&amp;showinfo=0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe><br />
<em>An impression of the final results of the Mobiserv project (2013).</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
